	<section id="platform">
		<h2>Platform</h2>
		<article>
			<p>If elected Treasurer, Richard Henderson plans to stay true to his simple upbringing and blue collar background 
			by teaching Kentuckians the importance of a fair and honest dollar. He plans to support the Financial Literacy 
			and Education Commission and work to create a treasury to high school financial literacy program.</p>

			<p>Richard is dedicated to the citizens of Kentucky and the stability of the state as a whole. Thatʼs why he plans 
			to serve on all boards that support the best interests of retirees, working men and women and all Kentuckians. 
			He will work tirelessly to search for and return as much unclaimed property to the people as possible. Richard 
			considers all Kentuckians to be members of his big family, so he will continue to protect the wellbeing of our 
			citizens first and find federal monies that should be used to enhance our communities here in Kentucky.</p>
		</article>
