			<p>Richard has been a Democratic member of the Kentucky House of Representatives representing District 74 since 2007. 
			During this time, he has worked to grow committee memberships, spent six years as a member of the Transportation 
			Budget Committee and four years on the Appropriations &amp; Revenue Budget Committee. Heʼs been the Vice Chairman of 
			Agriculture and Small Business all eight years and was Co-Chair of Energy for two years. Richard believes his 
			legislative and finance experience has uniquely prepared him for the job of State Treasurer.</p>

			<p>Before his tenure as a state representative, Richard was elected Mayor of Jeffersonville, KY. 
			During his four-year term, family values and community service were the focuses of his initiatives. 
			Richard successfully expanded the city park and water system, created events like Santa in the Park 
			and an Easter egg hunt and built much-needed modern sidewalks and highways for the city. Throughout his 
			political endeavors, Richard Henderson has also spent the past 18 years as a small business owner—acting 
			as CEO and CFO of C&amp;N Concrete (?).</p>
